Taco Bell hopes the “Cantina” restaurants it will serve will become urban hotspots
Do you want to spend an elegant evening in the city?
Taco Bell is an option.
On September 22, the Mexican-style fast food chain will open a new location in Chicago’s Wicker Park area, offering a tapas-style menu of appetizers, a fresco painted by a local artist, and even alcoholic beverages.
It is the first test location of the “Taco Bell Cantina” restaurants of the chain, which caters to young people, concentrations in increasing numbers in the centers of cities.
Taco Bell, which has nearly 6,000 restaurants in the U.S., has its roots mainly in the suburbs and is associated with cheap, fast-cooked food such as the extremely popular Doritos Locos Taco.
With an average Taco Bell bill of $7, the company used drive-through service and fast services to attract the number of customers needed to make a profit.
But Taco Bell says that in order to address the new generation that is “looking for more central urban environments in which to live, work and have fun,” test locations need to follow a different model, with smaller spaces and more expensive options.
In order to do a drive-through, you need the ground.
Can you imagine what it means to buy an acre of land in an area like Wicker Park?
“You can’t afford it,” Neil Borkan, the Taco Bell franchisee who will operate the Chicago location, told USA TODAY.
At the Chicago location, the new menu will be prepared alongside traditional Taco Bell offerings, in an open kitchen, where “you’ll be able to see the food yourself” before it’s prepared, Meredith Sandland, chief development officer at Taco Bell, told The Associated Press.
The new venue will also serve wine, beer and frozen alcoholic beverages, following the recent example of many of the Taco Bell competitors.
Now, seventy-five Starbucks cafes offer “evening” menus that include beer, wine, and snacks.
One thousand of the approximately 1,900 Chipotle restaurants offer alcoholic beverages.
The company said another Taco Bell Cantina location will open in San Francisco near AT&T Park this month, replacing drive-through service and parking with an interior yard and a sales window.
These changes in location, atmosphere and appendices indicate that the fast food chain wants to attract other types of customers than those who are looking for fast food at night.
Taco Bell decided for the first time on a higher quality culinary line in 2012, when it inaugurated more expensive Cantina and burritos menus to compete with Chipotle, the project being supported by an advertising campaign focused on the protein content of new dishes.
If successful, the Cantina restaurants will be another step towards a higher level.
Taco Bell said it plans to open 2,000 restaurants in the United States by 2022.
As Sandland told the AP, "a few hundred" of them will be of the "Cantina" type.
