At the national level, the petition has names from former Ministers of Education, such as Mircea Miclea, to people of culture who are also academics, such as Andrei Pleșu, Aurora Liiceanu or Alina Mungiu-Pippidi.
“Although the Education Law provides for the evaluation of doctoral schools, this fact has not been achieved to date, thus resulting in the lack of concrete sanctions for doctoral schools that flagrantly violate the ethical norms of scientific research and do not produce relevant and internationally recognized performance,” the petition states.
The petition specifically calls for compliance with the Law of National Education, the evaluation of doctoral schools, the suspension of the right of operation for any doctoral school in which more than two plagiarisms were found, until the assessment and remedy of the situation.
The last requirement is the suspension of the right of operation for any doctoral school in which there is no minimum number of doctoral leaders provided by law that meet the criteria imposed by the National Council of Scientific Research in 2011 for eligibility to grant IDEI-type projects.
Do you respect less a general without a doctorate, or a politician, or an intelligence agent in the Middle East?
"Why are there no other academies in Europe that give doctorates organized by the secret services, and top military personnel who give their doctorates do so at autonomous academic institutions, where quality is verified by the academic environment?" said Alina Mungiu-Pippidi, president of the Romanian Academic Society, initiator of the petition, also from Iași.
This can be completed by all applicants on the Society’s website, and the final signatures will be submitted by the organization to the Ministry of Education and Scientific Research.
